Rating: 4
I made this recipe with a few variations and it's one of my favorites! (as well as my friends') add the juice of one lemon. use 3/4 c each mayo and yogurt. use olive oil instead of canola. and fuji apples work great. makes good leftovers. make it simple with just cabbage and the sauce. it's always good.

Rating: 3
I made this with packaged coleslaw mix. The only changes I made otherwise were to omit the walnuts (which I didn't have) and to substitute a different variety of apple (spartan). Served 10 generously (with a small bowl left over). Guests really liked it. I made it a couple of hours ahead of our BBQ, which was convenient.

Rating: 4
This recipe is simply delicious, although I thought it was a little more time consuming to make than other reviewers. I made this for two parties and it was a hit at both. I made one addition and that was to add blue cheese to the dressing, the blue cheese goes really well with the apples and in my opinion makes this recipe even better. This is a must try.

