Rating: 2
I found this recipe to be very disappointing. I made it the day before serving, as the recipe suggested, and found that the walnuts got soggy and the salad took on uni-color, washed-out look. Even though it feeds a large crowd, if it is not appealing, what's the point?

Rating: 3
This makes a very large salad- I used about 2/3rds of the bagged coleslaw and added dried cranberries which added some nice color and taste. Great for a holiday potluck.

Rating: 4
I served this cole slaw at a party and everyone wanted the recipe to make it later. I sent people home with little containers of it for snacks. The only drawback is that this recipe makes LOTS of slaw, probably more than your family will need for half a week of servings.